WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.680
The C R M is the single place where every person, property, deal and conversation in the business is recorded. If it is not in here, it did not happen.

2
00:00:08.680 --> 00:00:20.120
All four businesses run inside it. ASAP Lending, H2M, the licensed team and transaction coordination share one system rather than four. The screens and the buttons are identical across all of them.

3
00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:28.400
This is your dashboard. It is the screen you land on every time you sign in, and its job is to answer one question before you have to ask it. What needs me today.

4
00:00:28.400 --> 00:00:34.460
It is not a summary of the business and it is not a report. It is a worklist, arranged in the order you should deal with things.

5
00:00:34.460 --> 00:00:41.730
At the top sits Needs attention. It holds two kinds of item. Tasks that are past their due date, and deals that have not moved in a while.

6
00:00:41.730 --> 00:00:51.400
The second kind matters more than it looks. A deal that has stopped moving is the most common way money is lost, and it never announces itself. Nobody calls to say they have gone cold.

7
00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:59.500
Each row tells you the client, what is wrong, which business it belongs to, and whose deal it is. Every row has a button, so you can act without leaving the page.

8
00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:09.440
Below that are your counters. Appointments in the next seven days. Closings this month. Active deals, with how many opened this month. Active properties. And revenue month to date against pace.

9
00:01:09.440 --> 00:01:15.510
These are live. They move as you work, so they are meant to be glanced at several times a day rather than studied once a week.

10
00:01:15.510 --> 00:01:21.870
Further down is a panel for multi product clients. These are people buying from more than one of our businesses at the same time.

11
00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:30.680
They get their own panel because those relationships are the hardest to win and the most expensive to lose. A bad experience on any one deal puts all of them at risk.

12
00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:34.890
Down the left is the rail. It is how you get everywhere, and it is grouped by business.

13
00:01:34.890 --> 00:01:45.420
You only see the businesses you work. Underneath them is a shared section that everyone has. Contacts, properties, calendar, communications, reports, commissions, follow ups and settings.

14
00:01:45.420 --> 00:01:54.300
If a whole section seems to be missing, that is almost always your access rather than a fault. Your seat controls which pipelines appear, and an owner can change it.

15
00:01:54.300 --> 00:02:04.830
Along the top right are the quick add buttons. A contact, a deal, an appointment or a logged call can be started from any screen, so you can capture something mid call without losing your place.

16
00:02:04.830 --> 00:02:14.120
Finally, settings. You have one login for everything. You sign in once through the Business Suite and that carries you into the C R M, the document hub, training and inventory.

17
00:02:14.120 --> 00:02:19.580
If you cannot get in, reset your password from the Business Suite sign in screen rather than from inside an app.
